<paragraph blockId="36.[189,428,264,291]" box="[189,428,264,291]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,428,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,428,264,291]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Taxonomic remark</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[188,1399,314,568]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
The description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[424,539,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[424,539,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 1998" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[546,1027,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta" subGenus="Montanocheila">
(
<emphasis box="[556,581,314,339]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[608,711,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">distincta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y." box="[721,1027,314,340]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="313 - 321" refId="ref48523" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Cheng X. - Y. 1998. New species and new records of hover-flies of the genus Cheilosia Mg. from China (Diptera: Syrphidae). Zoosystematica Rossica 7: 313 - 321." type="journal article" year="1998">Barkalov &amp; Cheng, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
agrees with the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunetti, 1915" authorityName="Brunetti" authorityYear="1915" box="[189,608,351,378]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticincta">
<emphasis box="[189,431,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Cheilosia hirticincta</emphasis>
Brunetti, 
<quantity box="[549,608,351,378]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8641" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="in" value="1915.0">1915</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in almost all described characteristics. The studied specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[189,262,389,415]" name="Nepal" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<specimenCount box="[275,383,389,416]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[442,579,389,415]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="female">six females</specimenCount>
, have basoflagellomere reddish-brown with light greyish dusting and blackish dorsal margin (described as black with greyish dusting in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[953,1173,427,453]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis box="[953,1173,427,453]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Cheilosia distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1226,1380,427,454]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticincta">
<emphasis box="[1226,1380,427,454]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">C. hirticincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The 
<collectionCode box="[241,309,466,492]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">NHM</collectionCode>
(London) has 
<specimenCount box="[478,575,465,491]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="male">six male</specimenCount>
specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunetti." authorityName="Brunetti." box="[857,1208,465,491]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticincta">
<emphasis box="[857,1098,465,491]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Cheilosia hirticincta</emphasis>
Brunetti.
</taxonomicName>
The structure of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[425,536,503,529]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,536,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[543,699,503,529]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta" subGenus="Montanocheila">
(
<emphasis box="[553,577,504,529]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[599,699,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[750,904,503,529]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticincta">
<emphasis box="[750,904,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">C. hirticincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar. However, we have not been able to locate and study the 
<typeStatus box="[505,555,542,568]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName box="[690,843,541,567]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirticincta">
<emphasis box="[690,843,541,567]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">C. hirticincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to evaluate a possible synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[1257,1390,541,567]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis box="[1257,1390,541,567]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">C. distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
